From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Albert Lloveras <albert.l@canva.com>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 1970 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix testidn path construction for forward-slash source dirs

testData() in icu4c/source/test/intltest/testidn.cpp has two issues that
manifest as TestDataFile failing with U_FILE_ACCESS_ERROR on Windows under
a Bazel build, where the source-dir path comes from Bazel runfiles and uses
forward slashes on every platform.

(1) The "is srcDir relative?" check only looks for U_FILE_SEP_CHAR, which is
`\` on Windows. Our srcDir contains forward slashes (e.g.
`C:/.../icudata-src-dir/`), so the check thinks the path is a bare filename
and prepends ".\\". The resulting path `.\\C:/.../sprep\\rfc3491.txt` is
malformed (mixed relative prefix and absolute drive-letter path) and Windows
refuses to open it. Extend the check so either separator counts.

(2) After `*basename++ = U_FILE_SEP_CHAR;` the buffer is not null-terminated
(the increment moved past the freshly-written separator). The very next
`uprv_strlen(filename)` then walks past the intended end into uninitialized
malloc memory until it finds a stray zero byte, basename ends up positioned
in garbage, and the next uprv_strcpy writes the next path segment in the
wrong place. Null-terminate after each conditional append.

Both issues are dormant in upstream Makefile builds: their srcDir already
ends with U_FILE_SEP_CHAR (so the conditional append never fires) and uses
platform-native separators (so the relative-path check correctly passes).

---
diff --git a/icu4c/source/test/intltest/testidn.cpp b/icu4c/source/test/intltest/testidn.cpp
index 1234567..89abcde 100644
--- a/icu4c/source/test/intltest/testidn.cpp
+++ b/icu4c/source/test/intltest/testidn.cpp
@@ -100,7 +100,7 @@
     pTestIDNA = &test;
     
     /* prepare the filename beginning with the source dir */
-    if(uprv_strchr(srcDir,U_FILE_SEP_CHAR) == nullptr){
+    if(uprv_strchr(srcDir,U_FILE_SEP_CHAR) == nullptr && uprv_strchr(srcDir,'/') == nullptr){
         filename[0] = 0x2E;
         filename[1] = U_FILE_SEP_CHAR;
         uprv_strcpy(filename+2,srcDir);
@@ -110,12 +110,14 @@
     basename=filename+uprv_strlen(filename);
     if(basename>filename && *(basename-1)!=U_FILE_SEP_CHAR) {
         *basename++=U_FILE_SEP_CHAR;
+        *basename=0; /* null-terminate so the next uprv_strlen() reads the right length. */
     }
 
     /* process unassigned */
     basename=filename+uprv_strlen(filename);
     if(basename>filename && *(basename-1)!=U_FILE_SEP_CHAR) {
         *basename++=U_FILE_SEP_CHAR;
+        *basename=0; /* same as above; defensive in case this block is ever reached. */
     }
     
     /* first copy misc directory */
